$ Oracle: V$DB_CACHE_ADVICE
@ v$db_cache_advice

`v$db_cache_advice` shows the simulated miss rates for a range of potential buffer cache sizes. 

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views[Oracle Dynamic Performance Views] (such as `→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/statistics_level`)

  The init parameter `→ development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters/db/cache/advice`.
